WEBVTT

00:11.171 --> 00:15.961
[man speaking indistinctly on radio]

00:23.191 --> 00:25.871
- Tucker, are you finished with breakfast?
- Mm-hmm.

00:25.921 --> 00:28.171
- Can you brush your teeth, please?
- Okay.

00:28.221 --> 00:30.981
Thank you.

00:32.661 --> 00:33.781
How are you doing over there?

00:33.831 --> 00:37.081
Where's Daddy?

00:37.131 --> 00:39.691
Daddy's at work.

00:39.741 --> 00:42.491
- For two days?
- I know.

00:42.541 --> 00:45.231
There's so many bad guys out there,

00:45.281 --> 00:47.991
but I bet you that he will be back

00:48.041 --> 00:49.861
when you get home from school.

00:49.911 --> 00:52.531
Show Daddy my drawing when he gets home.

00:52.581 --> 00:53.571
- Oh, I will.
- [knock at door]

00:53.621 --> 00:54.971
It looks so good.

00:55.021 --> 00:56.571
- What's this, again?
- It's a key.

00:56.621 --> 00:58.101
- Morning.
- A key.

00:58.151 --> 01:01.271
- Oh, I hear Uncle Julio.
- Hi, Uncle Julio.

01:01.321 --> 01:03.241
HEATHER: Put this picture
in a special place.

01:03.291 --> 01:05.551
- Tucker, Uncle Julio's here.
- Got your stuff?

01:05.601 --> 01:07.311
- Hey, buddy.
- Say good morning to your uncle.

01:07.361 --> 01:08.651
You guys ready to go? Hey.

01:08.701 --> 01:11.421
Hi. Thank you so much for taking them.

01:11.471 --> 01:12.951
You got it.

01:13.001 --> 01:14.761
Yeah, call me if you hear anything.

01:14.811 --> 01:16.421
Yeah. Yeah, I will.

01:16.471 --> 01:19.931
- Okay.
- Yep, I will.

01:19.981 --> 01:23.701
Hey, wait for me, guys.

01:23.751 --> 01:26.771
[woman speaking indistinctly on radio]

01:31.991 --> 01:35.841
- Come on, come on, come on.
- [phone line trilling]

01:35.891 --> 01:38.951
[cell phone ringing]

01:40.231 --> 01:42.381
I'm thinking it's his wife.

01:42.431 --> 01:43.821
She keeps calling.

01:43.871 --> 01:45.051
PERNELL: His wife?

01:45.101 --> 01:46.551
I told you he's married.

01:46.601 --> 01:48.691
I know you told me.

01:48.741 --> 01:52.331
God damn it.

01:52.381 --> 01:54.431
[cell phone rings, chimes]

01:54.481 --> 01:56.261
Did he have kids?

01:56.311 --> 01:58.931
Two.

02:00.781 --> 02:02.701
[sighs]

02:02.751 --> 02:05.011
What did I do?

02:05.061 --> 02:08.511
Having kids doesn't make Shane innocent.

02:08.561 --> 02:10.011
He confessed to me.

02:10.061 --> 02:12.711
He said it out loud, and he had to pay.

02:12.761 --> 02:14.151
That was God's command.

02:14.201 --> 02:16.321
Yeah, well, why didn't PJ wake up?

02:16.371 --> 02:17.551
I kept my promise.

02:17.601 --> 02:20.391
Why is my son still a
lump in a hospital bed?

02:20.441 --> 02:22.991
Hmm.

02:23.041 --> 02:25.961
Have you heard the story
of Saul and the Amalekites?

02:26.011 --> 02:28.961
I'm not in the mood for
Scripture right now, Keith.

02:29.011 --> 02:31.801
- I got to go.
- God told Saul

02:31.851 --> 02:35.241
to kill all the Amalekites, so he did.

02:35.291 --> 02:37.171
He wiped them out, except for one.

02:37.221 --> 02:40.511
He decided...

02:40.561 --> 02:42.081
to let the king live,

02:42.131 --> 02:44.411
so God rejected Saul,

02:44.461 --> 02:47.311
banished him to die.

02:48.931 --> 02:53.291
So I'm Saul in this story.
You think I pissed God off?

02:53.341 --> 02:56.521
I think maybe the job's not done.

02:59.811 --> 03:01.161
You talking about...

03:01.211 --> 03:04.401
whoever put Shane up to it?

03:04.451 --> 03:08.971
Maybe. Yeah.

03:11.121 --> 03:14.011
Yeah, at least Saul knew who he was after.

03:14.061 --> 03:15.941
All you kept saying is,
"They made him do it."

03:15.991 --> 03:17.611
Who the fuck is "they"?

03:17.661 --> 03:19.411
How the fuck am I supposed
to find out who "they" is?

03:19.461 --> 03:20.981
How did you find Shane?

03:24.871 --> 03:26.891
Get out of here. You need to go.

03:32.611 --> 03:36.001
Uh, hey, you want Shane's phone?

03:36.051 --> 03:38.361
No, get rid of it.

03:38.411 --> 03:40.631
And I mean fucking destroy it.

03:40.681 --> 03:43.901
[engine turning over]

03:48.461 --> 03:51.611
♪♪ [Fantastic Negrito's An Honest Man]

03:51.661 --> 03:55.221
[blues vocalization]

03:55.271 --> 03:58.921
♪ Now I'm in love again ♪

03:58.971 --> 04:00.521
♪ No, this time it's not ♪

04:00.571 --> 04:02.521
♪ With my hand ♪

04:02.571 --> 04:06.561
♪ Wandering, murdering ♪

04:06.611 --> 04:08.391
♪ Every time that I get ♪

04:08.441 --> 04:10.031
♪ The chance ♪

04:10.081 --> 04:13.831
♪ I'm a human ♪

04:13.881 --> 04:15.371
♪ But remember first ♪

04:15.421 --> 04:17.541
♪ I'm a man ♪

04:17.591 --> 04:18.911
♪ These streets ♪

04:18.961 --> 04:21.111
♪ Got me wandering ♪

04:21.161 --> 04:24.641
♪ Looking for my fix again ♪

04:24.691 --> 04:26.111
♪ I should've prayed ♪

04:26.161 --> 04:28.711
♪ The night before ♪

04:28.761 --> 04:30.151
♪ Now I'm losing ♪

04:30.201 --> 04:32.121
♪ Everything I have ♪

04:32.171 --> 04:35.461
♪ Yesterday it felt so good ♪

04:35.511 --> 04:37.061
♪ But now today ♪

04:37.111 --> 04:40.331
♪ It feels so bad ♪

04:40.381 --> 04:43.601
♪♪

04:48.281 --> 04:51.541
♪♪ [Anita Ward's
Ring My Bell plays on TV]

04:51.591 --> 04:54.641
♪♪

05:01.461 --> 05:03.381
- [knock at door]
- Come in.

05:03.431 --> 05:04.991
♪♪

05:11.271 --> 05:13.431
- ♪ I'm glad ♪
- Hey.

05:13.481 --> 05:15.201
♪ You're home ♪

05:15.251 --> 05:18.901
♪ Now, did you really miss me? ♪

05:18.951 --> 05:20.401
♪ I can't ♪

05:20.451 --> 05:22.041
I got to admit, I'm not too comfortable

05:22.091 --> 05:25.111
with this look you got going.

05:25.161 --> 05:27.571
Put some pants on?

05:27.621 --> 05:30.711
[chuckles] You don't have to stay, Josh.

05:30.761 --> 05:34.251
♪ While I put away the dishes ♪

05:34.301 --> 05:36.651
- ♪ Then you ♪
- [music stops]

05:36.701 --> 05:38.321
No. Come on.

05:38.371 --> 05:40.721
Shrimp basil or veggie fun?

05:48.411 --> 05:50.231
Hospital called.

05:50.281 --> 05:53.801
Pernell got the 48-hour stay extended.

05:53.851 --> 05:56.001
How long?

05:56.051 --> 05:57.341
Indefinitely.

05:57.391 --> 06:00.071
If I want PJ off life support,

06:00.121 --> 06:02.211
I got to go to court.

06:07.631 --> 06:10.381
I can help you find a great lawyer.

06:10.431 --> 06:12.991
There's no reason for you to put
yourself in Pernell's crosshairs.

06:13.041 --> 06:15.561
My best friend's on a ventilator,

06:15.611 --> 06:18.391
and we should be spreading
his ashes over Big Sur.

06:18.441 --> 06:21.561
And you're dancing disco half naked.

06:21.611 --> 06:23.001
Those aren't good enough reasons?

06:23.051 --> 06:25.131
[laughs]

06:28.321 --> 06:29.501
[crying]

06:32.561 --> 06:35.041
God.

06:35.091 --> 06:39.481
Hey, tell me what you want to do.

06:39.531 --> 06:41.181
I'll be right there with you.

06:41.231 --> 06:42.551
I don't know.

06:44.101 --> 06:45.421
I don't know.

06:47.841 --> 06:49.191
I don't know.

06:56.051 --> 06:57.361
I don't know.

06:57.411 --> 06:58.901
[sighs]

06:58.951 --> 07:01.901
[playing bright hymnal]

07:01.951 --> 07:04.741
♪♪

07:06.000 --> 07:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

07:19.771 --> 07:21.151
This is the one.

07:21.201 --> 07:23.361
I felt it as soon as I sat down.

07:23.411 --> 07:26.931
You said you were looking
in the $5,000 range.

07:26.981 --> 07:29.401
This one goes for $28,000.

07:29.451 --> 07:32.901
We have one over here I like
to call our Chrysler 300.

07:32.951 --> 07:36.271
Looks like a Bentley.
Doesn't cost like a Bentley.

07:36.321 --> 07:38.671
Probably doesn't drive
like a Bentley either.

07:38.721 --> 07:41.741
- It's in your price range.
- Ah...

07:41.791 --> 07:45.051
Sir, I'm sure you can see
what kind of work we do.

07:45.101 --> 07:46.711
Am I right?

07:46.761 --> 07:50.651
You know, there are some people
who won't listen to a man speak,

07:50.701 --> 07:54.821
but when they hear music and
open their mouths to sing,

07:54.871 --> 07:56.721
suddenly their hearts and souls are opened.

07:56.771 --> 08:01.891
And they receive the Word,
and their lives are saved.

08:01.941 --> 08:03.261
This piano...

08:03.311 --> 08:08.271
would be the heartbeat of that work.

08:08.321 --> 08:11.941
So I ask you right now,

08:11.991 --> 08:14.471
in the name of Jesus,

08:14.521 --> 08:17.611
to let God put a price in your heart.

08:17.661 --> 08:21.851
♪♪

08:21.901 --> 08:24.281
Now, tell me.

08:24.331 --> 08:27.351
How much do you want us
to pay for this piano?

08:27.401 --> 08:31.421
- I could do $25,000.
- [laughs]

08:34.140 --> 08:38.400
- What about installments?
- We'd need half up front.

08:38.451 --> 08:39.931
Why not start saving for this

08:39.981 --> 08:42.101
and get a piano you could
afford in the meantime?

08:42.150 --> 08:43.941
We don't want "in the meantime."

08:43.991 --> 08:47.541
Why don't we offer you a
space in our weekly program?

08:47.591 --> 08:50.481
It's typically a $500-per-week donation.

08:50.531 --> 08:53.181
We could give it to you for
free for the rest of this year

08:53.231 --> 08:54.751
and all of next.

08:54.801 --> 08:57.321
That plus the $5,000 would more than cover

08:57.371 --> 08:59.191
your asking price.

08:59.241 --> 09:01.251
How many members do you have?

09:01.301 --> 09:04.321
We're growing every day.

09:04.371 --> 09:06.431
I'm sure you are,

09:06.481 --> 09:08.761
but I don't think we can make this work.

09:10.251 --> 09:12.431
Robert Schuller used to preach

09:12.481 --> 09:14.131
out of the back of a station wagon

09:14.181 --> 09:15.741
at an old drive-in.

09:15.791 --> 09:20.141
He turned that into the Crystal Cathedral.

09:20.191 --> 09:22.381
Didn't they go bankrupt?

09:22.431 --> 09:24.541
[clears throat]

09:33.771 --> 09:35.761
Enough.

09:45.221 --> 09:48.271
[engine turning over]

09:51.921 --> 09:54.611
- Courtney.
- Good morning, Mrs. Harris.

09:54.661 --> 09:56.911
- Hi, Crystal.
- Welcome back, Mrs. Harris.

09:56.961 --> 10:00.581
The eyes are a bit out of
focus, but we'll fix it.

10:00.631 --> 10:02.351
I don't think it's the eyes.

10:02.401 --> 10:04.951
Look at the smile. It's
like he's hiding something.

10:09.611 --> 10:11.861
Keep going. I'll catch up.

10:13.541 --> 10:15.431
As I was saying, get rid of the buck teeth.

10:15.481 --> 10:17.301
Maybe draw some on the side.

10:20.281 --> 10:23.401
PERNELL: Your beard's
getting kind of scraggly.

10:26.821 --> 10:30.611
I used to have a longer
beard than that in college.

10:32.031 --> 10:33.951
Hippie beard.

10:35.531 --> 10:39.651
[monitor beeping]

10:59.361 --> 11:02.781
I think I know why you're not waking up.

11:12.301 --> 11:14.721
You don't want to talk to me?

11:14.771 --> 11:17.561
You know what I did for you, right?

11:17.611 --> 11:21.161
You do know what I made happen?

11:21.211 --> 11:23.731
I did that for you.

11:27.321 --> 11:30.901
I would do anything for you, PJ,

11:30.951 --> 11:33.871
but you're gonna have to
give me something to go on.

11:35.331 --> 11:38.281
- Who is "they," son?
- ♪♪ [campy upbeat music]

11:38.331 --> 11:40.611
♪ Jerry's Exotic Fish Store ♪

11:40.661 --> 11:44.021
♪ The best exotic fish store in the world ♪

11:44.071 --> 11:46.121
♪ Fresh water, salty
water, salty water, fresh ♪

11:46.171 --> 11:49.691
♪ Any water, any fish, Jerry's the best ♪

11:49.741 --> 11:51.191
♪ That fish store ♪

11:51.241 --> 11:53.361
♪ Jerry's Exotic Fish Store ♪

11:53.411 --> 11:56.401
♪ Best exotic fish store in the world ♪

11:56.451 --> 11:58.701
♪ Bring your whole family,
Jerry's always here for you ♪

11:58.751 --> 12:00.831
♪ Matching fish with people
is what he loves to do ♪

12:00.881 --> 12:04.141
WOMAN: Mr. Harris, we're
gonna need the room for a bit.

12:04.191 --> 12:05.811
Well, see what you can do

12:05.861 --> 12:09.481
about making that goddamn TV go off.

12:09.531 --> 12:12.851
[woman speaking indistinctly over PA]

12:14.901 --> 12:16.651
BOBO: Get the doctor on the
phone. Feel kind of sick.

12:16.701 --> 12:18.681
Stop wearing sneakers to the office.

12:18.731 --> 12:21.891
- I'm comfortable.
- It's embarrassing.

12:21.941 --> 12:25.431
- Sorry to keep you waiting.
- Did you start a new hobby?

12:25.481 --> 12:29.131
[chuckles] Those are for stress relief.

12:29.181 --> 12:32.471
Doctor says I'm supposed to
smash stuff when I get worked up.

12:32.521 --> 12:35.001
Asa took it upon himself to hijack
some poor classroom's mission project.

12:35.051 --> 12:37.441
Those kids feel special
now. It's a win-win.

12:37.491 --> 12:41.441
- Does it work?
- I'm not into busting up dollhouses.

12:41.491 --> 12:43.041
That's some white-people shit.

12:43.091 --> 12:45.651
Yeah, because you never hear
of black people having strokes.

12:45.701 --> 12:49.521
Well, I hope this
doesn't add to the stress,

12:49.571 --> 12:52.081
but wanted you to hear it from us.

12:52.131 --> 12:53.721
We've run into a bit of a snag.

12:53.771 --> 12:56.591
We're going to have to
postpone next week's pour.

12:56.641 --> 12:58.491
- [cell phone rings]
- Hello?

12:58.541 --> 13:00.661
- It's Toby. He...
- Yeah, not now.

13:00.711 --> 13:02.401
He'll call you back.

13:02.451 --> 13:06.371
We seem to be misunderstanding
each other a lot recently.

13:06.421 --> 13:10.471
[speaking Spanish]

13:10.521 --> 13:13.071
"Prefiere."

13:13.121 --> 13:14.541
English is fine. Thank you.

13:14.591 --> 13:16.511
Weren't we speaking English last week

13:16.561 --> 13:18.981
when you promised me no
more construction delays?

13:19.031 --> 13:20.511
And this is not just a delay.

13:20.561 --> 13:21.711
You're fucking with my concrete pour.

13:21.761 --> 13:23.381
You see why I'm confused.

13:23.431 --> 13:25.251
Well, this is out of our hands.

13:25.301 --> 13:27.251
There's a shortage of gravel.

13:27.301 --> 13:29.421
[laughs]

13:29.471 --> 13:30.991
You ran out of rocks.

13:31.041 --> 13:34.061
Special rocks.
Watsonville-McCoy number four.

13:34.111 --> 13:36.031
We're building so close to a seismic fault,

13:36.081 --> 13:38.161
we have to go with prestressed concrete.

13:38.211 --> 13:40.031
This gravel's just mandatory for the mix.

13:40.081 --> 13:42.841
When until we get these
magical earthquake rocks?

13:42.891 --> 13:45.511
Two, three weeks at the most.

13:45.561 --> 13:47.541
We'll keep you posted.

13:47.591 --> 13:49.981
Oh, you'll keep me posted.

13:50.031 --> 13:52.511
But if I call around
and luck up on somebody

13:52.561 --> 13:54.251
who has these rocks, then we're still good

13:54.301 --> 13:55.621
for next week, right?

13:55.671 --> 13:59.421
[speaking Spanish]

13:59.471 --> 14:02.621
Yeah, Pernell is not getting suspended,

14:02.671 --> 14:04.621
and you need to stop hitting
the brakes on this deal

14:04.671 --> 14:06.891
every time he gets a
goddamn parking ticket, man.

14:06.941 --> 14:08.761
It's time we make this
relationship permanent.

14:08.811 --> 14:10.561
We're not making anything permanent

14:10.611 --> 14:12.831
till we know Pernell's permanent.

14:18.791 --> 14:21.971
Get the presiding judge on the phone.

14:23.331 --> 14:24.581
You got his number?

14:25.631 --> 14:28.081
BOBO: It's a she.

14:30.001 --> 14:32.951
I did exactly what PJ
said. He never woke up.

14:33.001 --> 14:34.721
Not even a twitch.

14:34.771 --> 14:37.991
Not yet, but that doesn't
mean he'll never wake up.

14:38.041 --> 14:39.731
I get that... God's time and all,

14:39.781 --> 14:41.361
but you said I was on a righteous path.

14:41.411 --> 14:42.931
And I said you would be tested.

14:42.981 --> 14:46.601
We never know how long a path
is until we reach the end of it.

14:46.651 --> 14:48.101
How do I know this shit's gonna work?

14:48.151 --> 14:49.301
Well, you have to trust.

14:49.351 --> 14:51.471
- Like Simon did.
- Exactly.

14:51.521 --> 14:52.771
In Luke 5, Jesus pointed

14:52.821 --> 14:54.471
to the water and told Simon,

14:54.521 --> 14:55.881
"Drop your nets."

14:55.931 --> 14:57.741
Simon said, "You're crazy, man.

14:57.791 --> 14:59.851
I already tried that spot.
There's no fish there.

14:59.901 --> 15:02.381
I know 'cause this is what I do.

15:02.431 --> 15:04.151
I'm a fish expert."

15:04.201 --> 15:07.251
And Jesus said, "You know
what I'm an expert in?

15:07.301 --> 15:10.691
Listening to God."

15:10.741 --> 15:12.561
And when Simon laid down those nets,

15:12.611 --> 15:14.661
he caught so many fish,
the boat almost sank.

15:14.711 --> 15:16.531
You know what? Good for Simon.

15:16.581 --> 15:19.061
But I did what God said, and I got nothing.

15:19.111 --> 15:21.731
And I did way more than throw in some nets.

15:21.781 --> 15:24.001
CRYSTAL: Pernell...

15:27.361 --> 15:29.011
Oh.

15:34.261 --> 15:35.921
Hello.

15:43.741 --> 15:46.961
Don't mind me.

15:47.011 --> 15:51.131
You're Aunt Val called.
Dinner tomorrow night.

15:51.181 --> 15:53.631
She insisted.

16:11.771 --> 16:13.321
Maybe we should leave.

16:13.371 --> 16:16.821
Just hang on a second.

16:16.871 --> 16:19.961
Look, now, if God is testing my faith,

16:20.011 --> 16:23.101
He's not starting out with the easy stuff,

16:23.151 --> 16:25.701
so you're just telling me
just do whatever God says,

16:25.751 --> 16:29.071
even if... just do what He says,

16:29.121 --> 16:30.401
and PJ'll wake up?

16:30.451 --> 16:33.011
- If it's in God's plan.
- "If"?

16:33.061 --> 16:35.681
Well, "if" just isn't enough.

16:39.431 --> 16:44.221
If you follow God's instruction...

16:44.271 --> 16:46.151
PJ will wake up.

16:46.201 --> 16:49.191
I guarantee it.

16:59.951 --> 17:02.231
It'd be better if we
can talk in your office.

17:02.281 --> 17:04.101
I think it'd be better
if I was fucking Beyoncé,

17:04.151 --> 17:05.441
but I'm not Jay Z.

17:05.491 --> 17:07.070
And I'm not canceling my lunch

17:07.121 --> 17:09.641
for some shit you could've
told me over the phone.

17:09.691 --> 17:12.011
Shane Caldwell's missing.

17:12.060 --> 17:13.851
It's the cop.

17:16.131 --> 17:17.721
Sit down.

17:21.340 --> 17:23.461
When you say missing, you mean, like...

17:23.511 --> 17:26.761
1-800, "side of a fucking
milk carton" missing,

17:26.810 --> 17:28.060
like his wife is asking me

17:28.111 --> 17:29.631
why I brought him in for questioning.

17:29.681 --> 17:30.961
Maybe had something to do with that.

17:31.011 --> 17:32.631
Don't worry... I left out the part

17:32.681 --> 17:34.901
where you strong-armed me into
interrogating him for a lunatic.

17:34.951 --> 17:37.701
- I told her it was unrelated.
- No to "strong-arm." Yes to "unrelated."

17:37.751 --> 17:39.541
I made Shane strip naked for Pernell

17:39.591 --> 17:41.671
'cause he refused to believe
he didn't rape Jocelyn.

17:41.721 --> 17:43.211
How do I know he left it at that?

17:43.261 --> 17:45.241
That was a grieving father
in the heat of the moment.

17:45.291 --> 17:47.481
What you need to do is stop
looking for conspiracies

17:47.531 --> 17:50.421
and focus on finding Caldwell.

17:58.941 --> 18:02.031
[indistinct chatter]

18:06.851 --> 18:08.071
Save my place.

18:27.071 --> 18:30.721
So have you spoken to the Lord?

18:30.771 --> 18:32.391
You were right.

18:32.441 --> 18:35.531
He wants us to find out
who Shane was working for.

18:35.581 --> 18:37.701
But he didn't say who?

18:37.751 --> 18:38.901
I haven't figured that out yet,

18:38.951 --> 18:41.731
but the night Shane raped Jocelyn,

18:41.781 --> 18:43.741
he said he was on a vandalism case.

18:43.791 --> 18:45.241
The police have a file

18:45.291 --> 18:48.741
complete with pictures
of graffiti, everything.

18:48.791 --> 18:50.411
So you think Shane had help?

18:50.461 --> 18:52.381
I'm gonna start there.

18:52.431 --> 18:55.611
- KD.
- Yeah?

18:55.661 --> 18:59.221
- Donation time.
- Okay.

18:59.271 --> 19:00.951
Thanks, man.

19:03.041 --> 19:07.191
I got to go take my pee test.

19:07.241 --> 19:10.031
We can't meet here anymore.

19:10.081 --> 19:11.961
Somebody spots us, they're gonna ask

19:12.011 --> 19:14.771
a whole lot of questions
I don't want to answer.

19:14.821 --> 19:17.341
You got to move.

19:17.391 --> 19:20.841
Oh, oh, uh...

19:20.891 --> 19:23.181
I can't really move right now,

19:23.231 --> 19:25.181
but maybe...

19:25.231 --> 19:26.911
there's a phone booth not far...

19:26.961 --> 19:29.381
I'm not gonna call you. That's even worse.

19:29.431 --> 19:31.881
- You want to be my Benaiah?
- Yeah, you know I do.

19:31.931 --> 19:35.761
Well, then you're gonna have to move.

19:35.811 --> 19:37.561
They won't let me.

19:37.611 --> 19:40.031
Rules say I can't move unless I have a job.

19:40.081 --> 19:43.161
Well, what do you do? You
just sit on your ass all day?

19:43.211 --> 19:46.071
No, I'm not... I'm not lazy.

19:46.121 --> 19:48.231
I'm not lazy, Judge Harris.

19:48.281 --> 19:51.101
Men like me getting a job,
that's easier said than done.

19:51.151 --> 19:53.111
Oh, come on, man. Don't
be singing that song to me.

19:53.161 --> 19:54.971
I know there's programs for cons.

19:55.021 --> 19:57.611
I put in every week.

19:57.661 --> 19:58.981
Place like McDonald's will take you

19:59.031 --> 20:00.781
if you got a felony,
but not if it's violent.

20:00.831 --> 20:04.781
I got hired by a landscaper last week
until the background check came in.

20:04.831 --> 20:08.151
He fired me the next day. He said it
wasn't me, but if the customers find out...

20:08.201 --> 20:10.091
Keith, I'm not coming down here anymore.

20:10.141 --> 20:12.221
- You understand that?
- Then let me come to you!

20:12.271 --> 20:16.601
Please, please, don't...
don't cut me loose.

20:17.881 --> 20:19.061
You're my calling.

20:19.111 --> 20:20.371
All right, all right, settle down.

20:20.421 --> 20:22.001
I'm not cutting anybody loose.

20:22.051 --> 20:25.201
- You need a job?
- [exhales sharply]

20:25.251 --> 20:28.141
I may know somebody who's hiring.

20:30.431 --> 20:32.881
Thank you, Judge Harris.

20:36.971 --> 20:39.151
Hey, Keith.

20:41.901 --> 20:44.091
I keep seeing his face

20:44.141 --> 20:46.431
when I go to sleep at night.

20:50.011 --> 20:54.531
- That ever happen to you?
- No, sir.

20:54.581 --> 20:56.241
Shane was guilty,

20:56.291 --> 20:59.541
and he found Jesus before he died.

20:59.591 --> 21:02.941
I'm content with that.

21:04.931 --> 21:07.851
NICK: Why do you want to
take PJ off life support?

21:07.901 --> 21:10.151
Why not wait another two months? Two weeks?

21:10.201 --> 21:13.291
Because he can't be revived.

21:13.341 --> 21:14.721
JOCELYN: I mean, I mean, um...

21:14.771 --> 21:15.991
She deserves to move on.

21:16.041 --> 21:17.991
JOSH: So does PJ.

21:18.041 --> 21:19.891
And how do you play into this, Mr. Miller?

21:19.941 --> 21:22.361
- You two related?
- No, we're friends.

21:22.411 --> 21:26.671
PJ's my... was my best friend.

21:26.721 --> 21:28.101
I'm here to support.

21:28.151 --> 21:32.071
But this is your decision, Jocelyn, hmm?

21:33.791 --> 21:35.611
Listen, I can't imagine
what you're going through,

21:35.661 --> 21:37.411
and I know you want to do the right thing,

21:37.461 --> 21:40.881
but cases like this destroy people.

21:40.931 --> 21:43.181
That's the price. Nonnegotiable.

21:43.231 --> 21:45.651
And you're talking about
taking on the Harris family.

21:45.701 --> 21:48.421
I'm sure you know better
than me what that means.

21:48.471 --> 21:50.621
Oh, you don't think she can win?

21:50.671 --> 21:52.761
I don't think she's ready
for what it would take to win.

21:52.811 --> 21:55.431
You met her five minutes ago.
You don't know how strong she is.

21:55.481 --> 21:57.531
But I know you're doing all the talking.

21:57.581 --> 22:00.801
It's not a good sign. In fact,
why don't you step outside

22:00.851 --> 22:02.801
while I finish talking
to my prospective client?

22:02.851 --> 22:05.341
- Seriously?
- Or casually.

22:05.391 --> 22:08.041
As long as you end up on
the other side of that door.

22:10.991 --> 22:13.211
It's okay.

22:25.341 --> 22:28.291
Jocelyn, the people who win these cases

22:28.341 --> 22:30.961
walk into my office spitting fire,

22:31.011 --> 22:33.401
and I need that fire,

22:33.451 --> 22:35.731
because winning has just as
much to do with perception

22:35.781 --> 22:37.271
as it does with the law.

22:37.321 --> 22:39.201
I would have to trot
you out front and center

22:39.251 --> 22:42.171
to the media, the judge,

22:42.221 --> 22:45.141
and Heaven forbid we go
to trial, the jury too.

22:45.191 --> 22:47.481
This is not a dig,
certainly not a judgment,

22:47.531 --> 22:49.381
but you walked in my
office wearing flip-flops.

22:49.431 --> 22:51.281
You're not looking for a fight.

22:51.331 --> 22:54.121
You want this to be over.
There's no shame in that.

22:54.171 --> 22:58.391
A lot of people would say
it's the more enlightened path.

22:58.441 --> 23:02.291
So, if there's any way you
can get on with your life

23:02.341 --> 23:06.071
without going to court,
that's what I would do.

23:08.151 --> 23:10.371
Thank you for your time.

23:14.891 --> 23:18.081
[whirring]

23:26.601 --> 23:28.091
[shredder whirring]

23:30.541 --> 23:33.191
So this is the vandalism
report Shane filed?

23:33.241 --> 23:36.101
Doesn't say who made the 911 call.

23:36.151 --> 23:38.501
It was anonymous.

23:38.551 --> 23:41.171
What about the owner of the building?

23:41.221 --> 23:45.101
Report says she was out of town.

23:46.761 --> 23:48.671
[sighs]

23:50.561 --> 23:52.481
Wait a minute.

23:58.701 --> 24:01.551
- Who painted this graffiti?
- I don't know.

24:01.601 --> 24:04.491
We usually don't follow up on vandalism.

24:04.541 --> 24:07.031
Police reports are usually
for insurance claims.

24:07.081 --> 24:09.731
Anything particular you're looking for?

24:09.781 --> 24:11.301
I was hoping...

24:13.921 --> 24:16.601
Are you okay?

24:18.651 --> 24:21.711
Look, if you want me to do
some groundwork on graffiti,

24:21.761 --> 24:24.081
I'd be more than happy to.

24:24.131 --> 24:28.351
No, no, it's okay, Sergeant.
Thanks very much. You did plenty.

24:28.401 --> 24:31.451
Well, if you, uh...

24:31.501 --> 24:33.691
I'll be around if you need me.

24:40.441 --> 24:41.491
Judge.

24:45.911 --> 24:49.471
[device whirring loudly]

24:58.331 --> 25:00.181
- Shit.
- Hey.

25:01.661 --> 25:04.681
[sighs]

25:04.731 --> 25:07.121
I'll take care of this, Sister Alicia.

25:07.171 --> 25:08.351
Oh.

25:12.171 --> 25:14.591
Thank you.

25:19.351 --> 25:21.871
It's gonna be real nice
having you around, KD.

25:26.161 --> 25:28.571
There's a table in the back room.

25:30.791 --> 25:34.481
What's "100% Wood"?

25:34.531 --> 25:37.021
- What?
- Your tattoo.

25:37.071 --> 25:38.751
That's, um...

25:38.801 --> 25:41.421
from a long time ago.

25:41.471 --> 25:43.321
Hmm, eh.

25:43.371 --> 25:45.321
I got this when I was 16.

25:45.371 --> 25:48.561
It's supposed to symbolize my free spirit.

25:48.611 --> 25:51.401
Mm-hmm. It's pretty.

25:51.451 --> 25:54.131
- It's stupid.
- [grunts]

25:54.181 --> 25:56.741
What does yours mean?

25:56.791 --> 26:00.141
Oh, it's stupid too.

26:00.191 --> 26:01.571
Are you gonna tell me?

26:06.361 --> 26:08.751
It's a White Power gang.

26:08.801 --> 26:11.351
"Wood" stands for "peckerwood."

26:19.111 --> 26:20.561
Oh.

26:20.611 --> 26:22.961
That's not you anymore, is it?

26:23.011 --> 26:24.731
[grunts softly]

26:24.781 --> 26:28.301
That's all that matters.

26:36.291 --> 26:39.411
[metal creaking, squeaking]

26:50.771 --> 26:54.961
[monitor beeping]

27:08.561 --> 27:10.841
Maybe we should go get
a coffee or something.

27:10.891 --> 27:13.651
No, I'm okay. You can go, though.

27:13.701 --> 27:16.621
[metal creaking]

27:28.981 --> 27:32.961
You know they can't leave
any wrinkles in the sheets?

27:33.011 --> 27:34.931
Not even one.

27:35.951 --> 27:37.341
Wrinkles...

27:37.391 --> 27:40.371
Wrinkles cause uneven pressure,

27:40.421 --> 27:42.611
and he can get skin ulcers.

27:48.401 --> 27:49.851
Yeah, I think I will go get that coffee.

27:49.901 --> 27:53.891
I'm pretty sure that I could move on...

27:53.941 --> 27:56.921
even if they don't let me bury him,

27:56.971 --> 27:59.521
but then they'd have to do this to him

27:59.571 --> 28:03.431
twice a day, every day...

28:03.481 --> 28:06.031
till Pernell says so.

28:18.131 --> 28:22.551
Let's not let Aunt Val turn
this into an all-nighter, okay?

28:22.601 --> 28:24.881
"Did I ever tell you about the time... "

28:24.931 --> 28:28.021
Yes, Aunt Val, you told
us about the fucking time.

28:28.071 --> 28:30.361
[laughs] Believe me,

28:30.411 --> 28:34.531
if she pulls her, "Stay, have a brandy,"

28:34.581 --> 28:36.701
the answer's fucking no.

28:36.751 --> 28:40.671
♪♪ [soft pop music on radio]

28:46.121 --> 28:47.441
I would've blown her off,

28:47.491 --> 28:49.511
but I think she's been hearing stuff,

28:49.561 --> 28:52.441
so it'll be good for her
to see you're doing okay.

28:52.491 --> 28:54.511
Well, I am okay.

28:54.561 --> 28:57.321
I found Jesus. I'm not quitting my job.

28:57.371 --> 28:58.581
Okay.

28:58.631 --> 29:01.051
I'm not gonna walk away from everything

29:01.101 --> 29:04.721
we've built up and run
screaming into the woods.

29:04.771 --> 29:06.061
Okay.

29:06.111 --> 29:10.091
That's the second part she needs to hear.

29:10.141 --> 29:12.731
Then we can focus on
your lunch with Colette.

29:12.781 --> 29:14.831
I'm gonna join you... me and Bobo.

29:14.881 --> 29:16.671
Why, you think I need reinforcements?

29:16.721 --> 29:19.001
I think she needs to
understand how important it is

29:19.051 --> 29:23.681
that this judicial review
committee goes away.

29:23.731 --> 29:25.981
- Stop the car.
- What?

29:26.031 --> 29:27.951
- Back up. Back up!
- What? What's wrong?

29:28.001 --> 29:30.081
[tires screech]

29:30.131 --> 29:32.681
♪ That fish store ♪

29:32.731 --> 29:35.691
♪ Jerry's Exotic Fish Store ♪

29:39.171 --> 29:41.631
Pernell, what are you doing?

29:41.681 --> 29:43.631
♪ That fish store ♪

29:43.681 --> 29:47.571
♪ Jerry's Exotic Fish Store ♪

29:47.621 --> 29:49.371
♪ That fish store ♪

29:49.421 --> 29:50.941
You're really starting to scare me.

29:50.991 --> 29:53.071
Last time I was in PJ's room,

29:53.121 --> 29:54.741
this song came on.

29:54.791 --> 29:56.581
♪ That fish store ♪

29:56.631 --> 29:58.781
♪ Jerry's Exotic Fish Store ♪

29:58.831 --> 30:00.581
I haven't been able to
get it out of my head.

30:00.631 --> 30:02.551
I feel like it's PJ talking to me.

30:02.601 --> 30:06.591
It's not PJ talking to you, Pernell.

30:06.641 --> 30:10.251
- It's your conscience.
- Just tell me.

30:10.301 --> 30:14.831
I will as soon as you
get in the goddamn car.

30:14.881 --> 30:15.991
Now...

30:16.041 --> 30:18.631
Please.

30:23.891 --> 30:28.471
We came here to buy PJ
a fish for his birthday

30:28.521 --> 30:30.481
two years ago.

30:30.531 --> 30:31.681
You were furious with him

30:31.731 --> 30:33.711
for turning down a job at Brooks.

30:33.761 --> 30:35.811
You didn't want to buy
him a birthday present,

30:35.861 --> 30:36.951
but I insisted.

30:37.001 --> 30:38.581
Can we please get in the car now?

30:38.631 --> 30:40.891
It was rare fish.

30:42.701 --> 30:45.361
PJ wanted it for a long time.

30:45.411 --> 30:49.091
You had to order it special, right?

30:49.141 --> 30:51.231
Mm-hmm.

31:03.661 --> 31:08.481
Honey... please.

31:08.531 --> 31:10.681
Why did I care

31:10.731 --> 31:14.721
if my son didn't want to take a job?

31:14.771 --> 31:17.121
Why couldn't I just...

31:17.171 --> 31:20.121
let him be my son?

31:20.171 --> 31:21.931
Hey.

31:35.061 --> 31:36.341
What are you doing?

31:36.391 --> 31:37.941
I bought a little desk for KD.

31:37.991 --> 31:39.941
I thought he might like
to have a space of his own,

31:39.991 --> 31:41.651
you know, somewhere he can put his things

31:41.701 --> 31:42.851
or take a break.

31:42.901 --> 31:46.491
That's nice. He'll like that.

31:46.541 --> 31:48.221
I've been meaning to talk to you.

31:48.271 --> 31:50.991
I don't want you here
alone when KD's working.

31:51.041 --> 31:53.021
So, if you're gone the whole
day, I just don't come in to work?

31:53.071 --> 31:56.931
At least not for now, while
we're getting a feel for him.

31:56.981 --> 31:59.901
Paul, he's been coming here for six months.

31:59.951 --> 32:01.631
I think we know him by now.

32:01.681 --> 32:04.271
KD is a harmless, God-fearing man.

32:04.321 --> 32:06.341
He's a convict and an addict.

32:06.391 --> 32:08.611
You mean ex-convict, ex-addict?

32:08.661 --> 32:09.711
KD's damaged goods.

32:09.761 --> 32:11.141
You can feed a stray dog,

32:11.191 --> 32:13.751
but you don't take it home to your family.

32:13.801 --> 32:15.911
So why'd you hire him if you feel that way?

32:15.961 --> 32:17.421
Brother Pernell asked for a favor.

32:17.471 --> 32:19.121
What was I supposed to say?

32:19.171 --> 32:21.521
"Sorry. Why not see if they're
hiring at the post office?"

32:21.571 --> 32:22.751
People change by the grace of God.

32:22.801 --> 32:25.521
You are living testimony of that.

32:25.571 --> 32:27.661
You're showing your age right now.

32:27.711 --> 32:29.031
Really? Well, tell me this.

32:29.081 --> 32:30.631
If Oliver Stevens from
Tampa walked in here,

32:30.681 --> 32:32.101
would you have hired him?

32:32.151 --> 32:34.801
Don't you throw the
past in my face, Alicia.

32:34.851 --> 32:36.871
I'm asking you for something.
I've got good reasons.

32:36.921 --> 32:38.971
I've already seen him looking at you.

32:44.191 --> 32:46.381
Paul...

32:46.431 --> 32:49.711
- You know that I would...
- No, it's not that.

32:53.171 --> 32:55.121
I'm sorry. That was more
than it should've been.

32:55.171 --> 32:56.561
I'm just frustrated.

32:56.611 --> 32:59.091
Here you are, buying a new
desk for the new handyman

32:59.141 --> 33:01.961
on the payroll...

33:02.011 --> 33:06.361
and we can't even afford a proper piano.

33:21.401 --> 33:23.311
TESSIE: I thought I had the wrong address

33:23.361 --> 33:25.151
when I first got here.

33:30.271 --> 33:32.461
Well, if I asked you to
meet me at the office,

33:32.511 --> 33:34.061
I just think...

33:36.981 --> 33:38.901
I know.

33:46.391 --> 33:48.341
Okay.

33:48.391 --> 33:49.611
Well, I get public place,

33:49.661 --> 33:54.081
but why not a bookstore or a park?

33:56.101 --> 33:57.621
Well, I was hoping you could help me

33:57.671 --> 34:00.151
pick out a fish for PJ.

34:00.201 --> 34:01.951
Oh.

34:02.001 --> 34:05.221
I don't know too much about fish.

34:05.271 --> 34:08.831
I tend to stay away from
things that need feeding.

34:11.511 --> 34:14.130
PJ sent me a message.

34:16.420 --> 34:18.900
That's why I'm here.

34:18.951 --> 34:22.741
He's been talking to me,
sending me all kinds of visions.

34:24.690 --> 34:28.081
Does that sound crazy?

34:28.130 --> 34:30.051
I don't know.

34:30.101 --> 34:33.991
Part of me wonders if
there's always messages

34:34.041 --> 34:36.661
or signs we're missing.

34:36.710 --> 34:40.291
It's so easy to distract ourselves.

34:40.341 --> 34:44.031
Every now and then, something happens.

34:44.081 --> 34:49.031
Maybe you have a baby,
or there's an earthquake,

34:49.081 --> 34:51.900
- or somebody dies and...
- PJ's not dead.

34:51.951 --> 34:56.011
I'm just saying. Sometimes
things happen that make you stop

34:56.061 --> 34:57.911
and really pay attention.

34:57.961 --> 35:01.351
Maybe if I had paid more
attention before, he...

35:04.731 --> 35:06.991
Hey...

35:07.041 --> 35:08.751
thinking like that is not gonna help.

35:08.801 --> 35:12.361
Look at me.

35:12.411 --> 35:14.261
Just take what you can get.

35:24.521 --> 35:25.801
APRIL: So...

35:25.851 --> 35:28.471
tell me how you feel.

35:28.521 --> 35:30.041
I'm fine.

35:30.091 --> 35:32.711
Well, I don't have a blend for "fine."

35:32.761 --> 35:35.711
I need some emotion to go on.

35:35.761 --> 35:39.351
Um, pissed? Does that work?

35:39.401 --> 35:42.751
Shit. You don't want to say it out loud.

35:42.801 --> 35:44.721
What?

35:44.771 --> 35:46.861
Sad.

35:46.911 --> 35:50.731
That's a luxury I can't afford right now.

35:50.781 --> 35:52.861
Gatekeeper.

35:52.911 --> 35:57.271
Makes the bad feelings pass
and the good feelings last.

35:59.791 --> 36:03.741
[inhales sharply]

36:03.791 --> 36:05.411
Ooh, hoo-hoo, hoo-hoo.

36:05.461 --> 36:08.881
[laughs]

36:13.801 --> 36:15.421
Come on.

36:15.471 --> 36:17.461
They had to know they were
coming here to buy bunk beds.

36:17.511 --> 36:20.491
They're optimistic.

36:20.541 --> 36:22.531
The power of intention.

36:22.581 --> 36:23.761
Like The Secret.

36:23.811 --> 36:25.301
[laughs]

36:25.351 --> 36:27.471
Yeah, intention's not
gonna make that car bigger

36:27.521 --> 36:30.171
or the boxes smaller.

36:30.221 --> 36:33.341
Intention's not gonna make
that sadness go away either.

36:35.821 --> 36:38.381
I come for the weed,

36:38.431 --> 36:40.181
not the advice.

36:40.231 --> 36:45.051
- Ooh, I hope you cleared out your afternoon.
- Please.

36:45.101 --> 36:47.091
Some of us don't have time to bake cookies

36:47.141 --> 36:50.591
and talk about how good they are.

36:50.641 --> 36:52.621
Then you got a problem.

36:52.671 --> 36:55.961
I forgot to tell you.

36:56.011 --> 36:57.861
It's a one-hitter quitter,

36:57.911 --> 36:59.361
and you're on number three.

36:59.411 --> 37:03.531
[both laugh]

37:03.581 --> 37:04.801
Eh...

37:04.851 --> 37:07.011
[laughs]

37:07.061 --> 37:08.941
You set me up, you bitch.

37:08.991 --> 37:11.941
You're welcome.

37:11.991 --> 37:15.811
You need a break.

37:15.861 --> 37:17.351
You know what?

37:19.671 --> 37:22.251
It might run in my family... suicide.

37:25.341 --> 37:29.961
My mother tried it when I was 11.

37:30.011 --> 37:32.031
Fucked that right up too.

37:32.081 --> 37:33.871
Went and got her stomach pumped.

37:33.921 --> 37:35.671
I got up.

37:35.721 --> 37:38.041
I made breakfast,

37:38.091 --> 37:39.971
got my sisters to school,

37:40.021 --> 37:41.741
washed their faces,

37:41.791 --> 37:45.441
put ribbons in their hair.

37:48.431 --> 37:52.221
What am I doing now?

37:52.271 --> 37:54.321
Making sure Pernell's
where he supposed to be

37:54.371 --> 37:56.221
when he's supposed to be,

37:56.271 --> 37:59.991
even if it's only me
that's propping him up.

38:00.041 --> 38:04.531
Well, that all sounds very important...

38:04.581 --> 38:07.271
but your son shot himself,

38:07.321 --> 38:09.401
and that's real.

38:11.721 --> 38:16.041
No matter how much you
focus on propping Pernell up,

38:16.091 --> 38:19.141
sooner or later, the grief is going

38:19.191 --> 38:23.051
to have to be dealt with.

38:23.101 --> 38:25.621
So when are you gonna
find time to work that

38:25.671 --> 38:28.021
into your schedule?

38:31.371 --> 38:36.561
[man and woman chattering indistinctly]

38:36.611 --> 38:38.231
[cash register beeps, whirs]

38:38.281 --> 38:41.501
MAN: And here you are. Thank you, sir.

38:41.551 --> 38:44.471
[doorbell chimes]

38:48.091 --> 38:50.341
MAN: Hey.

38:53.031 --> 38:54.581
[tires screech, horns honk]

38:54.631 --> 38:56.381
Hey!

39:05.841 --> 39:09.961
- You need something?
- You know who painted this?

39:10.011 --> 39:11.431
I know who painted all of these.

39:11.481 --> 39:13.231
This one.

39:13.281 --> 39:15.601
I need to know who painted this one.

39:17.551 --> 39:19.201
ALL: ♪ One, two, three ♪

39:19.251 --> 39:20.601
♪ Get on your feet ♪

39:20.651 --> 39:22.841
♪ The time has come to feel the heat ♪

39:22.891 --> 39:24.741
♪ The pressure's rising around you ♪

39:24.791 --> 39:27.481
♪ Every day ♪

39:27.531 --> 39:29.711
♪ Four, five, six, get on your knees ♪

39:29.761 --> 39:33.081
♪ You've got to beg, you better plea... ♪

39:33.131 --> 39:38.321
This is graffiti from the police report.

39:38.371 --> 39:42.591
This is from the building
PJ... I mean, God sent me to.

39:42.641 --> 39:44.231
The same artist.

39:44.281 --> 39:45.761
He's working miracles through you.

39:45.811 --> 39:47.431
Mm-hmm.

39:47.481 --> 39:50.271
I need for you to get this guy.

39:50.321 --> 39:54.571
Julio Farkas. That's
where you can find him.

39:54.621 --> 39:57.111
I can do that.

40:01.861 --> 40:05.281
[indistinct chatter]

40:11.541 --> 40:13.121
[sighs]

40:16.711 --> 40:18.231
What did I miss?

40:18.281 --> 40:20.901
[Bobo clears throat]
Collette was explaining

40:20.951 --> 40:23.301
why she can't call off the
judicial conduct review.

40:23.351 --> 40:24.701
It's a committee decision.

40:24.751 --> 40:26.041
This is out of my hands.

40:26.091 --> 40:27.311
So who heads the committee?

40:27.361 --> 40:30.441
A violent felon signed a plea,

40:30.491 --> 40:33.541
and you still threw the
case out without explanation?

40:33.591 --> 40:36.081
There's no way that this
doesn't at least go to review.

40:36.131 --> 40:37.151
Who heads the committee?

40:37.201 --> 40:38.681
- I do.
- That's right.

40:38.731 --> 40:40.321
Because you're the presiding judge.

40:40.371 --> 40:42.321
Who made you the presiding judge?

40:42.371 --> 40:45.561
- I was elected.
- [chuckles]

40:45.611 --> 40:48.031
You didn't win your position.

40:48.081 --> 40:52.931
It was a gift from Pernell to you.

40:52.981 --> 40:54.001
And I will always be grateful,

40:54.051 --> 40:55.771
but I will not break the rules.

40:55.821 --> 40:59.371
Wow.

40:59.421 --> 41:03.841
Um, can I get a bottle
of Dos Maestros, 2011?

41:03.891 --> 41:05.041
You got it.

41:05.091 --> 41:08.051
We need some light in here.

41:08.101 --> 41:11.621
So how's Greg doing? I hear
the brewery's getting some buzz.

41:11.671 --> 41:14.051
Yeah, seems to be catching on.

41:14.101 --> 41:17.521
That's what Paul O'Neill over at San
Vicente Bank and Trust was telling me.

41:17.571 --> 41:20.791
I really admire people that
strike out on their own.

41:20.841 --> 41:23.831
Paul also mentioned something about, um...

41:23.881 --> 41:26.201
a cash-flow problem,

41:26.251 --> 41:30.371
that Greg was looking to
extend a line of credit...

41:30.421 --> 41:33.171
again.

41:35.991 --> 41:38.281
Boy, sure hope that works out.

41:39.761 --> 41:42.481
There's nothing I can do until the hearing,

41:42.531 --> 41:44.381
but then I promise I'm gonna make sure...

41:44.431 --> 41:47.721
There's not gonna be any public hearing.

41:47.771 --> 41:50.521
You're gonna handle this
in a closed-door session.

41:50.571 --> 41:53.721
[scoffs] I do that, people are gonna know

41:53.771 --> 41:55.361
that I'm giving you preferential treatment.

41:55.411 --> 41:58.101
I'll open myself up to an ethics review.

41:58.151 --> 42:00.101
That could happen.

42:00.151 --> 42:02.131
Probably won't, but it could.

42:02.181 --> 42:03.801
And if it does,

42:03.851 --> 42:07.411
well, then you know you
got me to protect you.

42:07.461 --> 42:10.111
The question you should
really be asking yourself is,

42:10.161 --> 42:13.311
if you don't side with us here,

42:13.361 --> 42:15.481
who's gonna protect you from me?

42:20.171 --> 42:22.751
Okay, wait.

42:22.801 --> 42:26.121
If you can get McCauley
to pull his complaint,

42:26.171 --> 42:27.561
I can make it all go away

42:27.611 --> 42:29.561
and not end my career in the process.

42:29.611 --> 42:31.431
Yes, we can get McCauley to back off.

42:33.051 --> 42:36.131
MAN: Wine's on the way. Ready to order?

42:36.181 --> 42:37.671
I was thinking halibut,

42:37.721 --> 42:39.901
but I don't want to offend
our little friend here.

42:39.951 --> 42:41.971
Oh, don't worry about him.

42:42.021 --> 42:43.811
He's coming with me.

42:43.861 --> 42:46.641
Aren't you? Enjoy the wine.

42:59.341 --> 43:03.161
I'm taking Pernell to court for PJ,

43:03.211 --> 43:04.931
and I want you to be my lawyer.

43:08.421 --> 43:11.171
ALICIA: It's beautiful.

43:11.221 --> 43:12.901
PERNELL: It's for PJ.

43:15.391 --> 43:18.511
He loves fish.

43:18.561 --> 43:21.781
That's a wonderful gesture.

43:21.831 --> 43:25.181
And I think it's great
what you did for KD too,

43:25.231 --> 43:26.881
helping him get a job.

43:29.401 --> 43:31.361
Of course things are gonna be much tighter

43:31.411 --> 43:34.561
now that he's on the payroll.

43:34.611 --> 43:37.201
$50,000 didn't loosen the noose enough

43:37.251 --> 43:39.301
to pay for a handyman?

43:39.351 --> 43:42.531
Well, that money's gone a long way already.

43:42.581 --> 43:44.241
You know we're putting in a new kitchen

43:44.291 --> 43:47.241
to feed the homeless thanks to you.

43:47.291 --> 43:50.111
We just didn't budget for a new employee.

43:50.161 --> 43:53.341
Are you asking me to write a check

43:53.391 --> 43:55.211
so that you can pay for KD?

43:55.261 --> 43:56.681
No, Brother Pernell,

43:56.731 --> 43:59.881
that's not what I had in mind at all.

44:09.481 --> 44:12.331
Have you ever heard Paul play the piano?

44:16.281 --> 44:18.271
Tell 'em who you are.
Tell 'em what you want.

44:18.321 --> 44:21.311
Okay.

44:21.361 --> 44:23.411
Hello.

44:23.461 --> 44:26.411
My name is Jocelyn Harris.

44:26.461 --> 44:30.511
My husband is Pernell Harris Jr.,

44:30.561 --> 44:33.951
and I'm fighting for the...

44:34.001 --> 44:35.491
- It's okay.
- Okay.

44:35.541 --> 44:38.891
I'm fighting for his
right to die with dignity.

44:44.411 --> 44:47.601
MAN ON TV: Why are you so determined
to have him taken off life support?

44:47.651 --> 44:49.431
I would much rather spend this time

44:49.481 --> 44:53.041
mourning the loss of my soul mate,

44:53.091 --> 44:57.381
but if honoring his wishes
means going to court...

44:59.061 --> 45:01.281
that's what I have to do.

45:01.331 --> 45:03.851
- Oh, fuck me.
- Thank you. That's all.

45:03.901 --> 45:06.851
Everything okay?

45:09.401 --> 45:11.151
Where the fuck is my piano?

45:11.201 --> 45:13.291
[scoffs]

45:13.341 --> 45:17.191
[discordant notes playing]

45:17.241 --> 45:21.031
[both moaning]

45:21.081 --> 45:22.301
[playing When We All Get to Heaven]

45:22.351 --> 45:25.441
[both moaning]

